I knew what was threatened, and off it came. But I had no hand in shipping that 
ivory arm there; that thing is against all rule”—pointing at it with the 
marlingspike—“that is the captain’s work, not mine; he ordered the 
carpenter to make it; he had that club-hammer there put to the end, to knock 
some one’s brains out with, I suppose, as he tried mine once. He flies into 
